def isToeplitzMatrix(matrix):
    rows = len(matrix)
    cols = len(matrix[0])
    for i in range(rows - 1):
        for j in range(cols - 1):
            if matrix[i][j] != matrix[i+1][j+1]:
                return False
    return True
```


    The algorithm iterates through each element in the matrix except the last row and last column. For each element, it checks if it is equal to the element on the bottom right diagonal. If any such pair of elements is not equal, the matrix is not Toeplitz and the function returns false. If every pair of elements is equal, the matrix is Toeplitz and the function returns true.

